===Verb===
'''career'''
#To move rapidly straight ahead or rather as the on line OED says the verb form is:career:     move swiftly and in an uncontrolled way in a specified direction : the car careered across the road and went through a hedge. PHRASES in full career archaic at full speed. ORIGIN mid 16th cent.(denoting a road or racecourse): from French carrière, from Italian carriera, based on Latin carrus ‘wheeled vehicle.’


